U = Z^2
Z
U = Z^2
\chi^2(1)
f_Z(z) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-z^2/2}, \quad -\infty < z < \infty.
F_U(u) = \Pr[Z^2 \le u] = \Pr[-\sqrt{u} \le Z \le \sqrt{u}] = 2 \int_{z=0}^\sqrt{u} f_Z(z) \, dz.
f_U(u) = 2 f_Z(\sqrt{u}) \frac{d}{du}[\sqrt{u}] = \frac{1}{\sqrt{u}} f_Z(\sqrt{u}) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi u}}e^{-u/2}, \quad u > 0. 
